<chapter id="bugs-chap">
	<title>Bug Tracking Systems</title>
	<para>Introduce bug tracking, the Debian BTS, and Malone.</para>

	<sect1>
	  <title>Bug Tracking</title>

	  <para>One thing that you will almost certainly face as a
	  packager is a bug, either in the software itself or in your
	  packaging. Packaging bugs are often fairly easy and
	  straightfoward to fix. However, as packagers often act as the initial
	  contact for software bugs for the users of their distribution
	  they also many time implement temporary fixes and are
	  responsible for forwarding software bugs and fixes to the
	  original (upstream) authors. In order to track these bugs (both
	  software and packaging) many distributions have developed bug
	  tracking systems to manage the bug reports and notify the
	  package maintainers and reporters of changes. The table below
	  shows some of the Debian and &ubuntu; tools for tracking
	  bugs.</para>

	  <informaltable frame="none">
		<tgroup cols="3">
		  <thead>
			<row>
			  <entry></entry>
			  <entry>Debian</entry>
			  <entry>&ubuntu;</entry>
			</row>
		  </thead>
		  <tbody>
			<row>
			  <entry>Bug tracking system</entry>
			  <entry>
				<ulink url="http://bugs.debian.org">http://bugs.debian.org</ulink>
			  </entry>
			  <entry>
				<ulink url="http://launchpad.net/malone/distros/ubuntu">http://launchpad.net/malone/distros/ubuntu</ulink>				
			  </entry>
			</row>
			<row>
			  <entry>Bugs for specific packages</entry>
			  <entry>http://bugs.debian.org/<emphasis>&lt;packagename&gt;</emphasis>			
			  </entry>
			  <entry>use search at above link
			  </entry>
			</row>
			<row>
			  <entry>Bugs for source packages</entry>
			  <entry>http://bugs.debian.org/src:<emphasis>&lt;packagename&gt;</emphasis>
			  </entry>
			  <entry>https://launchpad.net/distros/ubuntu/+source/<emphasis>&lt;packagename&gt;</emphasis>/+bugs
			  </entry>
			 </row>
			<row>
			  <entry>Package information</entry>
			  <entry><ulink
			  url="http://packages.debian.org">http://packages.debian.org</ulink>
			  or
			  http://packages.qa.ubuntu.org/<emphasis>&lt;packagename&gt;</emphasis>
			  </entry>
			  <entry>https://launchpad.net/distros/ubuntu/+source/<emphasis>&lt;packagename&gt;</emphasis>
			  for source packages
			  </entry>
			</row>
		  </tbody>
